isungen absieht.  aStaged photography - do practices of recourse that lead to a blurring of speaker, memory structure and perception contain the potential to re- and dis-organize?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Okt 2018) 4aArt History. 4aArt. 4aBildbezüge. 4aDéjà Vu. 4aFine Arts. 4aFotografie. 4aInszenierte Fotografie. 4aIntermediality. 4aIntermedialität. 4aInterpictoriality. 4aInterpiktoralität. 4aIntertextuality. 4aIntertextualität. 4aKunst. 4aKunstgeschichte. 4aKunsttheorie. 4aKunstwissenschaft. 4aPhotography. 4aPictorial References. 4aRita Nowak. 4aSam Taylor-Johnson. 4aStaged Photography. 4aTatiana Antoshina. 4aTheory of Art.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2018z9783110602999oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.14361/9783839443873zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783839443873.jpg  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA14ALL  aPDA15STM  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA3STM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DADb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017